         <abstract>
            <p>The Jacobi matrix of the (2n + 1)-point Gauss-Kronrod quadrature rule for a given measure is calculated efficiently by a five-term recurrence relation. The algorithm uses only rational operations and is therefore also useful for obtaining the Jacobi-Kronrod matrix analytically. The nodes and weights can then be computed directly by standard software for Gaussian quadrature formulas.</p>
          </abstract>
